<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Readonly Route</title>
    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
        background: linear-gradient(160deg, #fef3c7 0%, #f8fafc 100%);
        color: #1f2937;
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      }

      main {
        max-width: 640px;
        padding: 32px;
        border-radius: 20px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
        border: 1px solid rgba(180, 83, 9, 0.18);
        box-shadow: 0 24px 50px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
      }

      h1 {
        margin-top: 0;
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
        line-height: 1;
      }

      p {
        margin-bottom: 0;
        font-size: 1.03rem;
        line-height: 1.75;
        color: #4b5563;
      }

      code {
        padding: 0.15rem 0.35rem;
        border-radius: 6px;
        background: rgba(180, 83, 9, 0.1);
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>Readonly route</h1>
      <p>This file is mapped specifically for <code>/readonly</code> on the second server. It exists to confirm that the location block resolves to the correct file path.</p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>